chess in the West.  Alekhine was challenged by Botvinnik for a world
championship match in 1946, but the champion died a few days later. Important
decisions were made during a FIDE meeting in 1947. The world championship
would be organised under the auspices of FIDE. Botvinnik, Smyslov, Keres,
