capitalism and communism. Public interest for the mad genius was enormous.
Spassky was respected, because he had a score of +3, =2 against Fischer.  The
'match of the century' started on 11 vii 1972 with the usual time limit of 40
moves in 2 1/2 hours. An audience of 2300 spectators followed game one in the
Laugersdalholl stadium.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. e3 O-O 6.
